'''Richard Ofori''' (born 24 April 1993) is a Ghanaian professional footballer who plays for [[S.C. Covilhã]] as a [[defender (association football)|Defender]].

==Club career==
Born in [[Accra]], Ofori played youth football for [[Mighty Jets F.C.]], signing a one-year loan contract with [[Charleroi SC|Charleroi]] in 2011.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://ghanasoccernet.com/charleroi-sign-mighty-jets-captain-ofori|title=Charleroi sign Mighty Jets captain Ofori|publisher=Ghana Soccer Net|date=1 September 2011|accessdate=7 June 2016}}</ref> Ofori made his competitive debut for Charleroi against [[A.F.C. Tubize|Tubize]] on 29 Abril 2012 in the [[2011–12 Belgian Pro League|Belgian Pro League]]. 
Ofori then signed, on 21 January 2013, a six months loan contract with [[Lierse S.K.|Lierse]].<ref>{{Cite web | url=http://www.lierse.com/en/news/richard-ofori-signs-lierse-0 |title=Richard Ofori signs for Lierse|publisher=Lierse S.K.|date=21 January 2013|accessdate=9 June 2016}}</ref> He made his debut from the start in a 2-0 defeat to [[S.V. Zulte Waregem|Zulte Waregem]] on 26 January 2013.

On 2 September 2013, Ofori was signed by [[Associação Académica de Coimbra – O.A.F.|Académica]] and was immediately sent on loan to [[S.C. Beira-Mar|Beira-Mar]].<ref>{{Cite web | url=http://www.tvi24.iol.pt/beira-mar/academica-richard-ofori-mercado-ganes-beira-mar-maisfutebol/1485746-1467.html |title=Académica contrata promessa ganesa para ceder ao Beira-Mar|publisher=[[TVI 24]]|language=Portuguese|date=2 September 2013|accessdate=9 June 2016}}</ref>

